      <prompt>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <div>A 67-year-old man presents to Accident and Emergency with burns to 50% of his body after a traffic accident. His ECG shows tented T waves and small P waves.</div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>A 75-year-old woman is admitted to hospital with increasing lethargy, polyuria and polydipsia. She has a history of advanced lung cancer.</div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div>A 57-year-old man at preoperative clerking is shown to have U waves. He is on furosemide for high blood pressure.</div>
          </li>
