  <modalFeedback identifier="CORRECT_FEEDBACK" outcomeIdentifier="GENERAL_FEEDBACK" showHide="show">
    <p>
      <b>Option J (Hyponatremia) is Correct.</b>
      SIADH (syndrome of inappropriate ADH secretion) is a condition mostly found in patients diagnosed with small cell lung cancer, brain tumours, chest infections and strokes. The result is hyponatremia, and consequently headaches, nausea, vomiting and confusion.
    </p>
